        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:49PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 546 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong to severe
thunderstorm near Laurinburg, moving northeast at 15 mph. This storm
will weaken as it moves across the area but remaining capable of
producing strong wind gusts and hail.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 to 50 mph and up to half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Maxton and Wakulla.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
